    • Constructor Detail

      • Conference

        public Conference(Videobridge videobridge,
                  java.lang.String id,
                  EntityBareJid conferenceName,
                  long gid)
        Initializes a new Conference instance which is to represent a conference in the terms of Jitsi Videobridge which has a specific (unique) ID.
        Parameters:
        videobridge - the Videobridge on which the new Conference instance is to be initialized
        id - the (unique) ID of the new instance to be initialized
        conferenceName - world readable name of this conference
        gid - the optional "global" id of the conference.

      • describeShallow

        public void describeShallow(ColibriConferenceIQ iq)
        Sets the values of the properties of a specific ColibriConferenceIQ to the values of the respective properties of this instance. Thus, the specified iq may be thought of as a description of this instance.

        Note: The copying of the values is shallow i.e. the Contents of this instance are not described in the specified iq.

        Parameters:
        iq - the ColibriConferenceIQ to set the values of the properties of this instance on

        public JSONObject getDebugState(boolean full)

      • getDebugState

        public JSONObject getDebugState(boolean full,
                                java.lang.String endpointId)
        Gets a JSON representation of the parts of this object's state that are deemed useful for debugging.
        Parameters:
        full - if specified the result will include more details and will include the debug state of the endpoint(s). Otherwise just the IDs and names of the conference and endpoints are included.
        endpointId - the ID of the endpoint to include. If set to null, all endpoints will be included.

      • isP2p

        public boolean isP2p()
        Whether this looks like a conference in which the two endpoints are using a peer-to-peer connection (i.e. none of them are sending audio or video). This has false positives when e.g. an endpoint doesn't support p2p (firefox) and both are audio/video muted.

      • isInactive

        public boolean isInactive()
        Whether the conference is inactive, in the sense that none of its endpoints are sending audio or video.
